<v Speaker 1>And what what are we going to do if he stays?

00:08:44.740 --> 00:08:46.980
<v Speaker 1>I think you're getting the gist now.

00:08:47.140 --> 00:08:48.180
<v Speaker 2>Mood tense.

00:08:48.180 --> 00:08:49.540
<v Speaker 1>Mood tense.

00:08:49.640 --> 00:08:53.800
<v Speaker 1>So it's not just the structures that we are identifying, it's the feeling.

00:08:53.800 --> 00:08:55.800
<v Speaker 1>This is very important for the mood tense.

00:08:55.800 --> 00:09:00.200
<v Speaker 1>What you want to really get your head around is the feeling of the mood tense.

00:09:00.200 --> 00:09:02.120
<v Speaker 1>So you can start experimenting

00:09:02.440 --> 00:09:08.280
<v Speaker 1>About where you would use it and listening out for where you hear people using it.

